{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-14","name":"Ralph de Wilington","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Ralph de Wilington","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Ralph"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Wilington"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Ralph De Willington","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1239–1294","fullLifespan":"about 1239–Bef 15 October 1294","birthDate":"+1239","birthPlace":{"address":"Sandhurst, Gloucestershire, England","geo":{"latitude":51.9043,"longitude":-2.2489,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"England","geo":{"latitude":52.4379,"longitude":-1.6496,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nRalph was of full age in July 1260. He married Juliane and they had five sons: John (1st Lord Wilington), Reynold (clerk), Henry, Thomas, and presumably Edward. \n\nRalph de Wilington, son and heir, a minor at his father's death, was recognized as being of full age, July 1260. Supporting the Barons in the Civil War, 1264-65, he served under Geoffrey de Lucy and was appointed Keeper of Lundy Island, July-October 1364. He recognized a debt in October 1270; was probably the Ralph de Wilington who served for the Bishop of Lincoln in 1277; was named as a creditor, 12 February 1284/5; and was living, 6 May 1286.\n\nRalph de Wilington married Juliane, said to be daughter and apparently heir or coheir of Sir Richard de Lomene, of Uplowman, Devon. He died before 15 October I294. Juliane was living in June 1299, but was dead by 16 November 1323.","sourceList":[{"title":"Ralph de Willington, \"Find A Grave Index\"","sourceType":"FSREADONLY","sourceLink":"https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QVGH-YVGH","sourceUri":"9BP8-L2T"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1239","date":"about 1239","place":"Sandhurst, Gloucestershire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1256","date":"Bef 18 November 1256","place":"